The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Frontpage | 4 held in Ribhu murder case; Rs 8 lakh recovered
                                                                                                           4 held in Ribhu murder case; Rs 8 lakh recovered
                                  
	New Delhi, Jul 30 (UNI) : A day after the body of 16-year-old schoolboy Ribhu Chawla was found near a public school in Vasant Kunj in south Delhi, police today arrested four people for the gruesome murder and recovered ransom money of Rs 8 lakh from their possession, police said.  
	Rishi, Manni, Gaurav and Rocky, all aged between 19-21 years, were arrested during raids in different parts of Delhi and Haryana. Police also impounded the Wagon R car used in the crime. During interrogation of the quartet, it came to light that Rocky was known to Ribhu and other three were the formers friends. Though police recovered Ribhus mobile phone, which the abductors were using for making ransom calls to his father, they were yet to get hold of his schoolbag.  
	Police had fanned out its teams to Haryana from where some ransom calls were made to the father of Ribhu, a resident of Vikaspuri who was abducted on Tuesday afternoon.                                                                                                                                             
